                        <h5>Salient features of Margin Trade Funding</h5>
                        <p>
                            Margin funding allows the investors to take leverage positions in the Stock Market wherein clients must pay margin of 50% depending upon the scrips and rest is funded by TFL. To put it simply, in case of scrip’s prescribed for 50% margin, client pays cash margin of Rs.50,000/- and client can buy shares worth Rs.1,00,000/- with the balance Rs. 50,000/- being funded by TFL. Margin can be provided in cash as well as approved securities.
                            <br /><br />Scrips : Funding only against approved securities as per the list approved by the Transwarranty Finance Management from time to time.
                            <br /><br />Interest : Rate of interest will be 18% p.a. on the amount of funding availed for actual no of days.<br /><br />
                        </p>
                        <h5>Benefits</h5><br />
                        <p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Corporate Action benefits of Bonus, Dividends, Split Shares, Rights Issue etc will continue to accrue to the borrower.</li>
                                <li>Any appreciation in the value of the Securities given as margin would automatically allow enhancement in drawing power.</li>
                                <li>Interest will be calculated on the amount utilized & the actual period for which it is utilized.</li>
                                <li>Clients can view their financial statements and holdings online.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </p><br /><br />
